3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Orderly Network calculates RUNE/USDT funding rates hourly using a premium/discount mechanism based on perpetual-spot price divergence. The shared order book aggregates liquidity from multiple DEX frontends, creating more stable funding calculations compared to isolated exchanges. Funding payments occur automatically through smart contracts, with rates typically ranging from -0.5% to +2% during high volatility periods. The platform's infrastructure layer ensures consistent rate calculations across all connected frontends."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","RUNE","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RUNE's role in cross-chain liquidity provision creates predictable funding rate patterns, especially during network upgrades or major DeFi events. The token's correlation with broader DeFi sentiment makes it ideal for arbitrage strategies that capitalize on sentiment-driven funding imbalances. Orderly's shared liquidity model provides better rate discovery for RUNE compared to fragmented DEX liquidity."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RUNE/USDT funding rates on Orderly Network show strong correlation with THORChain network activity and cross-chain volume. During major DeFi protocol launches or Bitcoin volatility spikes, funding rates often turn negative as traders hedge DeFi exposure. Monthly analysis reveals funding rates average +0.05% during normal conditions but spike to +1.5% during network upgrade announcements. The hourly settlement creates more frequent arbitrage windows compared to 8-hour funding on centralized exchanges."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The most profitable RUNE funding arbitrage occurs between Orderly Network and centralized exchanges during liquidity crunches. Orderly's shared liquidity model often maintains tighter spreads, creating funding rate differentials of 0.3-0.8% with isolated DEXs. Cross-chain arbitrageurs can exploit funding differences between Orderly's NEAR/ETH deployment and other chains. The platform's white-label infrastructure allows monitoring rates across multiple frontends simultaneously for optimal entry points."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RUNE's inherent volatility can cause rapid funding rate reversals, particularly during THORChain governance votes or security incidents. Orderly's dependency on frontend partners creates operational risks where funding calculations might be affected by individual frontend issues. The shared order book model, while providing liquidity benefits, can amplify funding rate volatility during network congestion. Cross-chain bridge risks also impact RUNE arbitrage strategies when moving between Orderly and other chain deployments."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are RUNE/USDT funding rates updated on Orderly Network?","answer":"Funding rates are calculated and paid hourly on Orderly Network, providing more frequent settlement than most centralized exchanges. This creates additional arbitrage opportunities but requires more active position management."},{"question":"What makes RUNE funding rates different on Orderly's shared liquidity model?","answer":"Orderly's shared order book aggregates liquidity from multiple DEX frontends, creating more accurate price discovery and typically more stable funding rates. This reduces the extreme rate spikes seen on isolated liquidity pools."},{"question":"Can I arbitrage RUNE funding between Orderly frontends?","answer":"No, all frontends using Orderly Network share the same order book and funding rates. Arbitrage opportunities exist between Orderly and other exchanges, not between different Orderly-powered platforms."},{"question":"How do THORChain events affect RUNE funding on Orderly?","answer":"Major THORChain developments like network upgrades or new chain integrations typically drive RUNE funding rates positive as speculative demand increases. Cross-chain liquidity events can create temporary funding spikes of 1-2%."}]}]
